posts.body: Nice, seeded. Thanks.
Woah, nice. Thanks man.

Finally got this zeronet stable for myself. Guess it's time to start posting some stuff I have. Is there a suggested way to scrub any file/image watermarks (that are threatened to exist) from source images from patreon? Resize them all into a different file format maybe?

>>746fe619-ab9d-4fd6-988c-ca8224079a1b
Thanks I'll give it a try.

I've got them all OK and fully seeded with an open port. Just got zeronet going on a mini-device so I can leave it going 24/7. Maybe try deleting the bad ones (little triangle next to file name) and starting from scratch. Thats what I had to do to get the last two to download fully.

>>3de6a519-2349-4211-8c46-cd64aa1bf07d
Yeah and if I'm identified as the leaker I get kicked off pateon and can't leak anymore. One model threatens legal action if she "catches your pics" online. I know that's probably bogus, but wanted to see if there was an easy way to scrub however they mark. 

TLDR, just found zeronet, love whats posted and wanted to contribute some stuff I see missing. Just want to know the right way to do it, if there is one.

>>49a7b024-2e19-4a58-a216-449e113f8f52
What are these screenshots from?

>>15861950-ea40-429e-9523-d8b6c034f261
Yeah I have a several where it's either a dropbox link via PM and the Dropbox folder has my username in it, or it's emailed to my patreon email address in a zip file. So tracking is possible. Just trying to put some thought into reasonable counter measures.

Can we go back to discussing counter measures to tracking methods? Thats what started this discussion. Just want to be able to keep getting new sets if i start sharing them, and not be banned from patreon. Some models like to threaten legal action but i know thats very unlikely. Banning is much quicker.

I've also wondered if just releasing a slightly different image resolution could be used to identify people, much in the way photographers you hire give you reduced resolution images so they can prove some "rights" to them but keeping the full rez pics. 

Anyway, how would reducing image resolution impact pixel watermarks?

So check out her patreon for realz. But will still post stuff anyway.

Clothed ver

>>4c154bba-3cd8-4383-8c73-db4f39592850
I believe the x/100 means x% out of 100% downloaded, and then the next number is the number of seeders. Could be wrong. Also yeah the zeronet engine tends to lag alot and you have to let the page sit and update to see the real status. Wish they would/could disconnect the local render engine from the backend engine so having a bunch of transfers going doesn't bog down browsing.
Going offline for a bit as I have to go on travel. Will continue seeding and posting in about a week. Sitting at 2.1 ratio right now, zeronet only works if you keep it running people.

Good fiber connection here too. Pi might work. I'm being weird and actually running on a Ubiquiti CloudKey Gen2+. Mostly because It was free to me, I already use it to manage a bunch of networks and I don't use it as a security camera DVR so that 500GB hard drive is sitting there doing nothing. Runs Zeronet OK, as it's only a 2Ghz CPU. Really wish Zeronet was written to be multi threaded so it could use all 8 cores instead of just 1, and it would be much more responsive. At least Tor is running on a second core. 

Only runs off 7 Watts.

posts.subject: Unresponsive if you seed all files on a board
posts.body: I made the mistake of trying to seed all small and big files on a board that apparently is mostly 0 peers. I've been stuck "updating 14000 files" for a week now and it's very unresponsive. How do I cancel trying to sync all those files?

>>b2720c60-8430-4a35-99b5-bc1632d19b2b
O god thank you. For as big as Millchan is getting that should very much be a button somewhere when you bite off more than you can chew and nearly DDOS yourself.

>>94b9961a-1eb7-426a-adbd-402426e16a6f
Hmm. I don't think that's my problem and I wonder if there's some confusion on "file downloads". IE, file downloads meaning download operations from your own zeronet peer to your computer through a browser, or file operations meaning zeronet peer pulling files from other peers. I don't see how a browser limit is causing hellozero not to load when it is the only thing my browser is trying to load and I can plainly see the python and tor processes pegged at 100% CPU. Even with no browser trying to load a page.

>>ec2e3caa-00ed-4a74-b316-ff0557dc4f9c
> assume ZeroNet will eventually give up and stop trying to download "bad files" but it seems it's taking an excessive amount of time/tries sometimes.

EXACTLY! Should timeout after 24 hours.
Awesome thanks for uploading.

>>2ef9f703-5c77-4da5-b2fa-abbdc831a5d5
No i just saw that video on her youtube so can't be.

posts.body: Was it this?
Vandy is a photographer. Disharmonica is a model. She's modeled a bunch for him. I originally found her through some of his shoots.
God I love new Disharmonica sets. Thanks a bunch.
OOoo what did they do? I would like to see more discussion on counter-detection to avoid loosing leakers.
I am seeding them 24/7. If you can't get them it's on your end.
Also down. The key is accountability. We need to verify whoever is collecting the payments is posting the content.

>>33a68c26-d080-465b-b4eb-45cfe3a5fa7d
You sir are awesome!

>>e377382e-814e-4ed0-8682-f3a3daba31d4
Mine shows 9 per file. Champ.
These just got put on instagram. Damn she knows a way to one up herself without spoiling it doesn't she?

posts.subject: Wrong Board
posts.body: Wrong Board. Thats Nichameleon

>>c6ba2c05-2342-4ae4-974d-8d2e87ac4b88
Do you run in Tor only mode? That could do it too. That limits you to only peering with a subset of peers.
Awesome Thanks. I wish her patreon was more reasonably priced, as I would def be supporting her if it were.

>>6b159aed-6b8a-4d99-90d8-75bcc4d87851
Damn we are going to have to start this pool the money thing then. How should we do it? Paypal? Something more anonymous than that? Hopefully not crypto.

Everyone who'd be willing to pitch in, would you only do it if we kept the photos exclusive to the pool group or would you still contribute if they were posted here? 

Trying to figure out the next hardest part, how do we distribute.

>>9522455d-e3f8-4125-8028-1f5f85146d2b
Yeah if you want to run it I'll send you money. You want to post a paypal address? I suggest keeping a running list here published of who's sending you money to keep people honest. Maybe just a few initials of their paypal email?

>>c37291af-eaac-449e-9531-25034bbaf434
Wait seriously? How can that be? 
Another way yto do this is rotations, everyone interested takes a turn being a patreon supporter for a month, grabs and posts the stuff, and then unsubscribes the next month. 
No need for us to figure out sending money around, just need to get a list going for who's doing what month/girl.

>>78493dba-78be-4706-9a8b-f881fc4b1221
How is sending $12.50 a month for a year different than spending $150 once per year? Same money out, same stuff back.

This is not a new concept. 

Movie piracy in the late 90s and early oughts were FTP server communities. You had something like a 5:1 download/upload requirement to be a user of the FTP server. AKA you could download 5 movies for every 1 that you rented, ripped, compressed and uploaded.  This forced users to contribute and made the community successful. 

We could use the same model here. Everyone pays for 1 girl for 1 month a year, get multiple girls real long in return. No need for posting trackable paypal or otherwise links. No crypto. Just commitment to do your share.

>>e619cdb3-e692-4a20-96b3-97e0867fd5ab
Dude seriously. Setup a $12/month transfer to your own paypal. Sign up for Jessica $150 tier in Dec 2020. 

You get fired? Fine, tell us, keep the money in your paypal, sign up for a new date in the future when you get paid again. 

It's like you are TRYING to have issue with this.

Alright I'm genuinely interested if we can use ZN recreate old piracy FTP servers. 

Idea: 

We use Zeronet Mail for management. You email me what your willing to pay per year and what girl you are interested in. I'll coordinate and when we get enough post an assignment sheet here in a spread sheet. You'll get a girl and a month assigned. 

Files will be gzip'd with encryption and uploaded here by those assigned to do so (i'll post instructions to follow). Decryption keys will be Zeronet mailed around to the active members of the pool. 

If you miss your assignment, you fall off the active member list and no longer get mailed decryption keys. 

Pros: no one to trust with your money. No need to coordinate sending money anonymously. Worst case is you spent one month on patreon and got all the pcis for it. 

Cons: Yeah you have to spend $150 in one month. I got it. Use a savings account to build up your money till your assignment. Make note of this need when you sign up. I'll try to assign you to a later month to let you build up. 

My ZN mail address is devsci@zeroid.bit Send me a starter message if you are interested.

>>a9c5a7ca-1025-40e0-af3a-b87ea5868af1
Don't participate then. No one is forcing you. I have yet to see you suggest any ideas that you could support.

>>8b399336-3df8-4508-9b8c-b05e039247fe
Paypal failed. Too many against cypto. How do you suppose we do money transfer that is anonymous and shut-down proof? 

My scene idea is tested and true. Those ftp servers were very successful till bitorrent took over. I was in one many years ago, for many years.

>>7ffead47-632e-4a99-ba01-0c866580ec3f
ZeroMail is on your Hello homepage. Just activate it and follow prompts to setup a mailbox. After that it's like email. 

>>6eaac70c-b246-48a3-92af-f5466378054e
No idea. Not may people are offering up ideas and trying to get them started, and then a few people are just shitting on ideas without offering solutions/alternatives.

>>645f3e19-8fcd-4de8-a221-138124898695
 >>9186e979-1619-4797-b3b4-881f36459fef
I agree no discord. Keep everything Zeronet, then we maintain all the defense against takedowns. 

>>2eb4b519-3ec8-48ed-9d91-0dcca88541e4
I would like to see it shared too, but that only works out if we get enough contributors to maintain the status quo.

>>84ffc2a2-48d9-4554-b214-4d096213fdb9
Nobody has figured out an open payment method, or seems to be willing to take charge of an open method. A few have sent me zn mails and we've been discussing options for a private pool method. Maybe if it get shaken out it will turn into an open pool. 

For now though send me a zeronet message if you want in.  devsci@zeroid.bit 

You activate and use ZeroMail from your homepage.

>>14700dc3-ef4f-4d85-86a2-985f1d25cb6b
Did you create a username/address? Mine took 30 mins to an hour to sync after I did before that button worked.
For those that sent me an Zmail about the group buy, hang tight. Holidays and family bogged me down. Will respond by Wednesday with a plan.

>>d44661f8-5e93-42d0-bebe-b9f70aa3966a
O GOD I've been fighting ZN to complete this set, it looks so awesome. But it just won't do it.

>>2e37f45a-23bd-4e87-9e15-1df89aae0137
It's more than half the set for me. Maybe just re-up the whole set and trash the first. I run a 24/7 seed box so once I get the whole thing we are golden.

I love nonsummerjack, but seeing as these sets and all her sets are easily available on the regular internet, there's not much point in posting them here. 

For example, this set at the same quality is here: https://e-hentai.org/g/1546058/42ed0b21c5/

>>203b3716-fb7e-48e4-aff5-a7a1aeeea126
I've noticed photo-shopped blurriness on her ass for several months of sets now. She's hiding some blemish or is otherwise self conscience about it. Shame, I wish she'd stop that.
Damn I missed something I guess. Don't see anything new.

>>2f60bf12-b95c-44d8-8eec-0c209b067db1
Agree. She was perfect shape before, now it's too fake.
She's blurred her ass for months, maybe more than a year. This isn't new.

>>549d0043-77e6-4335-a0ab-9269e65b54de
Yeah sorry that hasn't gone anywhere yet. Holidays, family, work travel all have gotten in the way. I need to set time aside to figure out how that will work and respond to the Znmails.
